                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the south wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> (called the <hi rend="italic">Mukkōṭi-ēkādaśi-pradakshiṇa</hi>) in the Veṅkaṭēśa-perumaḷ temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>[Jaṭāvarmaṉ] Sundarapāṇḍya I.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This fragmentary inscription contains portions of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the king commens cing with <hi rend="italic">Samasta-jagad-ādhāra</hi> etc. It mentions the regnal year 7 in line 4.</p>						
                            
